text: Valkeala is a former municipality in Kymenlaakso, Finland. In 2003, 11,238 people lived there. It has an area of 1,004.40 km². In 2009, the six municipalities Anjalankoski, Elimäki, Jaala, Kouvola, Kuusankoski and Valkeala were merged to form the city of Kouvola. Valkeala is known for Repovesi National Park.
